{
  "message": "feat(deps): add d3 v7.9.0 and @types/d3 v7.4.3 for RaptorQ article visualizations\n\nAdd the D3.js data visualization library and its TypeScript type definitions\nas project dependencies. These are required by the new RaptorQ article's\ninteractive visualization components, which use D3 for rendering animated\nparticle systems, matrix visualizations, and data-driven diagrams that\nillustrate fountain code concepts (encoding matrices, Gaussian elimination\nsteps, and symbol transmission flows).\n\n- d3@^7.9.0: Full D3 suite including d3-selection, d3-scale, d3-transition,\n  d3-force, d3-interpolate, and all sub-packages for SVG/Canvas rendering\n- @types/d3@^7.4.3: Complete TypeScript type definitions covering all 30+\n  D3 sub-modules (d3-array, d3-axis, d3-brush, d3-chord, d3-color,\n  d3-contour, d3-delaunay, d3-dispatch, d3-drag, d3-dsv, d3-ease,\n  d3-fetch, d3-force, d3-format, d3-geo, d3-hierarchy, d3-interpolate,\n  d3-path, d3-polygon, d3-quadtree, d3-random, d3-scale,\n  d3-scale-chromatic, d3-selection, d3-shape, d3-time, d3-time-format,\n  d3-timer, d3-transition, d3-zoom)\n\nThe bun.lock file reflects the resolved dependency tree including transitive\ndependencies such as delaunator, robust-predicates, internmap, iconv-lite,\nsafer-buffer, and commander (used by d3-dsv's CLI tools).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
